Currently UILayoutComponent contains booleans and separate values to represent type and value for position/size. Also it have separate values for margins for some reason.

It would be much simpler to leave only next values and calculate layout based on them:

```
HorizontalEdge _horizontalEdge;
PositionType _positionTypeX;
float _positionX;
SizeType _sizeTypeWidth;
float _width;

VerticalEdge _verticalEdge;
PositionType _positionTypeY;
float _positionY;
SizeType _sizeTypeHeight;
float _height;
```

Where:

```
enum class PositionType {
    ABSOLUTE,
    PERCENT
}

enum class SizeType {
     ABSOLUTE,
     PERCENT,
     RELATIVE_TO_PARENT
}
```

And that will cover all possible situations much simpler, including fixed margins that currently is not possible. 

Though to write it correctly it will require to break backward compatibility...

